  "title": "Vision Systems Engineer (Halcon/OpenCV/VisionPro, East)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Develop, integrate, and optimize machine vision systems for automation equipment, including component selection (lighting, lenses, cameras) and system calibration.</li>\n  <li>Perform image processing and analysis using vision software such as Halcon, OpenCV, or VisionPro to ensure accurate and reliable inspection results.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot, debug, and improve machine vision performance in collaboration with cross-functional engineering teams.</li>\n  <li>Prepare documentation and provide technical support related to vision system design, testing, and implementation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Computer Science, Image Processing, Automation, Optics, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of hands-on experience in <strong>machine vision development and system integration</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in<strong> vision tools (Halcon, OpenCV, VisionPro)</strong> and strong understanding of vision components.</li>\n  <li>Good communication, problem-solving skills, and ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R21100996</p>",
